# Releases and versioning

## When bumping version

Update **every** location that reports the app version. Search for the current version string before and after.

Typical locations:

| Location | Example |
|----------|---------|
| `packages/core/package.json` | `"version": "0.7.8"` |
| `apps/api/package.json` | same |
| `apps/web/package.json` | same |
| `README.md` | version badge |
| `apps/api/src/config/openapi.ts` | `API_VERSION` |
| `apps/api/src/routes/health/index.ts` | hardcoded `version` |
| `apps/api/src/routes/health/schemas.ts` | OpenAPI examples |
| `apps/web/src/components/Layout.tsx` | sidebar `v0.7.x` |
| `apps/web/src/pages/setup/SetupPage.tsx` | `APP_VERSION` |
| `docs/support-questionnaire.md` | example version |

## Release notes

Create `docs/release-notes/vX.Y.Z.md` following the v0.7.7/v0.7.8 structure:

1. Title + one-line summary (maintenance vs feature release; baseline version)
2. **At a glance** table
3. **Summary for users** and **Summary for admins**
4. Database migrations section (even if “none”)
5. API/operator notes
6. Update instructions (Docker + operator checklist)
7. Full changelog (notable commits since previous release)

## Branching

- Day-to-day work merges to **`dev`**; **`main`** receives release merges.
- Ensure local `dev` tracks **`origin/dev`** so pushes trigger CI on the correct branch.
